      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That humming noise usually means the compressor is trying to start or run while the fan motor is stuck or seized, which is a serious mechanical issue. Before you go out there, you should definitely check if the unit is tripped at the circuit breaker or if there's a power outage, as a dead unit won't make that specific sound. If the breaker is fine, it is generally safer to wait for a professional technician rather than risking injury from electrical components or refrigerant leaks. You can call a local HVAC service to come out and inspect the fan motor and capacitor.",
